data.name: Label1.Text
data.value:
A constellation is an area in which a group of stars form a perceived outline or pattern, typically representing an animal or mythological creature. People of the past often used constellations and interpretations of them to explain the world around them.
The origins of constellations likely go back to prehistory. Most of the constellations we know today were named by the Ancient Greeks, after stories and characters from their mythology.
